From 24f1be97d97366663621fe973d95ac7773045d5d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: just4honey <j4f@list.ru>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 21:10:28 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] fix: preserve Cyrillic in wikilink resolution
 (normalizeBasename + resolveSlug)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- normalizeBasename: add Cyrillic (U+0400-U+04FF) + CJK (U+4E00-U+9FFF) to keep-chars
- makeResolver.norm: delegate to normalizeBasename instead of inline regex
- extract.ts inline slugify: add Cyrillic + CJK to keep-chars
- resolveSlug: add slugified fallback when direct comparison fails
- Enabled link_resolution.global_basename=true in config

Without this patch, [[wikilinks]] pointing to files with Cyrillic names
(e.g. [[people/Лобачева Екатерина Владимировна]]) always resolve to null
because the slug (people/лобачева-екатерина-владимировна) doesn't match
the raw path from the wikilink.
